<NewsPageTitle>
    Maintenance release: Blazorise 1.7.6
</NewsPageTitle>

<Paragraph>
    The Blazorise 1.7.6 maintenance release brings a collection of bug fixes, documentation updates, and minor enhancements aimed at improving stability and developer experience across components. This update addresses multiple community-reported issues, especially in data handling, charts, and component rendering.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>
    This release addresses key issues related to the <Strong>DataGrid</Strong>, <Strong>Markdown</Strong>, <Strong>Video</Strong>, and <Strong>Navbar (BarToggler)</Strong> components, ensuring a smoother development experience. Notable improvements include enhanced Markdown file upload handling, better DataGrid cell focus behavior, and fixes for the Seeking event in the Video component. Additionally, several UI inconsistencies affecting <Strong>FluentUI, Tailwind, and Bulma</Strong> frameworks have been resolved. Read on for the full list of changes.
</Paragraph>

<NewsPageSubtitle>
    Key Highlights in 1.7.6
</NewsPageSubtitle>

<Heading Size="HeadingSize.Is3">
    DataGrid: Missing Columns on Null First Row
</Heading>

<Paragraph>
    Fixed an issue where DataGrid failed to generate columns if the first row contained <Code>null</Code> values. The column detection now checks all rows, ensuring consistent rendering with dynamic data.
</Paragraph>

<Heading Size="HeadingSize.Is3">
    Chart: Crash with Zoom Plugin
</Heading>

<Paragraph>
    Resolved a critical exception when using the Chart component with the zoom plugin. The fix improves compatibility and ensures stable chart interactions during zooming.
</Paragraph>

<NewsPageSubtitle>
    FileEdit: AOT Compilation Fix
</NewsPageSubtitle>

<Paragraph>
    Fixed a System.NotSupportedException in FileEdit when used in AOT-compiled environments. The component now supports AOT properly and can be used in precompiled deployment scenarios.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>
    We encourage you to update to version 1.7.6 to benefit from these fixes and improvements. As always, please report any issues or provide feedback to help us continue improving.
</Paragraph>

